basics.name: Jonathan Keane
basics.label: Aspiring ML Researcher
basics.summary: Aspiring researcher with M.S. in Machine Learning and B.S in Computer Science. Interested in explainable and interpretable AI systems to promote ethical use of advanced technologies. Seeking research opportunities to further develop expertise in the fast-evolving AI field.

work.name: Direct Supply
work.summary: Worked on multiple data science and ML systems for senior living solutions. Led and collaborated on projects involving embeddings, LLM evaluations, and AI-based search.
highlights: Built menu planning tool with AI-based recommendations
Led RAG-based product type suggestion system using Databricks, Postgres (pgvector), and AWS
Developed AI-powered product search system; became company trade secret

work.name: CPA Leadership Institute
work.summary: Created a software tool to automate sending personalized LinkedIn messages using Python, Java, Selenium, and MySQL. Saved hundreds of hours in manual marketing.
highlights: Designed GUI for managing and sending LinkedIn messages
Implemented autocomplete contact search feature
Delivered SaaS solution sending over 5,000 automated messages

projects.name: Mentor – Computer Vision Soccer Analysis
projects.summary: Mentored undergraduates building a computer vision system for player stats extraction. Helped develop CNN and segmentation framework; project won 3rd prize in innovation challenge.
highlights: Guided YOLO and SAM 2 integration for player tracking
Built CNN-based field keypoint detection model
Helped team present and compete successfully

projects.name: Limiting Lying for RL Agents in a Social Deduction Game
projects.summary: Trained reinforcement learning agents with reward decomposition for the social deduction game Coup to identify and eliminate deceptive behavior. Implemented the environment and league-based training in Python with PyTorch LSTMs.
highlights: Literature review on interpretability in RL
Implemented Coup environment and LSTM agents
Developed strategy masking technique for honesty in agents

projects.name: Deep Learning Music Transformer Undergraduate Research
projects.summary: Explored Transformer architectures for music generation using the ROSIE supercomputer. Presented findings in a regional conference and won 1st place in innovation challenge.
highlights: Performed literature review on Transformer mechanisms
Developed training automation using Slurm on ROSIE supercomputer
Presented and published research results

projects.name: Slime Particle Simulation
projects.summary: Created a GPU-parallelized simulation of slime mold particle dynamics using CUDA C. Used real-time visualization via CUDA GL and explored food-type differentiation.
highlights: Implemented physarum polycephalum particle simulation
Optimized GPU performance with CUDA parallelism
Produced visual real-time simulation output

projects.name: MSOE NCAA Men’s Soccer Team
projects.summary: Captain and lead tutor balancing athletics and academics. Led training, organized tutoring, and built leadership and communication skills through competition and mentorship.
highlights: Captain and study tables lead tutor
Organized team practices and tutoring sessions
Developed teamwork and leadership under pressure

projects.name: MSOE Competitive Programming Team & Leadership Roles
projects.summary: Active involvement in programming competitions and community service initiatives.
highlights: ICPC National Competition 2022 & 2023 participant
FIRST FTC Robotics Mentor (2023–2024)
Google Developer Student Club Co-Lead (2021–2022)
Walnut Way Servant Leadership Project participant (2020–2021)
